               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18170917-246-person1695">
                  THOMAS 
                  SAMBROOK
               <interp inst="t18170917-246-person1695" type="surname" value="SAMBROOK"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18170917-246-person1695" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18170917-246-person1695" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a pawnbroker, and live at Marylebone. On the 28th of August, when I came home I found the coat had been cut down, I hung it up and in about a quarter of an hour I saw it fall down again, I went over the way and watched, and saw several young men come up-it hung inside the shop, the prisoner came up held his apron up and let it fall in - He ran off. I secured him. I never lost sight of him.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18170917-246-person1696">
                  GEORGE 
                  COBB
               <interp inst="t18170917-246-person1696" type="surname" value="COBB"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18170917-246-person1696" type="given" value="GEORGE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18170917-246-person1696" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a chinaman. I was in my shop and saw the prisoner take the coat.</p>
